TopicTitle: The Ones That Didn't Make It

Articles.Content:
For every craft I put out, there's a dozen that I don't, whether it was because it exploded or it just didn't look right. So I've selected the best of the worst! Take a look, and vote on which one(s) you'd like to see me complete.

Curiosity Mars Science Laboratory

![HSRoRUU.png](http://i.imgur.com/HSRoRUU.png)

The N1 Russian Moon Rocket (kept on overheating and exploding.)

![1Wuv01D.png](http://i.imgur.com/1Wuv01D.png)

NASA Warp Drive Concept 

![r5A2Pcf.png](http://i.imgur.com/r5A2Pcf.png)

Atlas/Mercury Rocket (Thrust-to-weight issues)

![kPzbNVM.png](http://i.imgur.com/kPzbNVM.png)

STS (oh god why why does it not fly pls to help)

![pyYqTM2.png](http://i.imgur.com/pyYqTM2.png)

Thanks for viewing, and cast your votes!

If we can get enough braincells and seconds, I bet most of these would fly wonderfully! ![:D](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif)

Care to extend out to inigma for diagnosing your STS?

I vote for the MSL.

Kill the cat!

bonus points if you get the reference
